<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880216-0131 </DOCNO><HL> Retail Sales Increase in Britain </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EUROP </CO><DATELINE> LONDON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   British retail sales, calculated on a volume basis, rose 10% in January from a year earlier and a seasonally adjusted 0.7% from December, the Department of Trade and Industry said in a provisional report.    In the three months ended in January, sales rose 6.5% from the year before and 1% from the prior three months.    On a value basis, January sales increased 11% from a year earlier. </TEXT></DOC>